    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Discretization error factor exceeds requirements (achieved level 3 vs. required level 2). Validation results demonstrate CFD model predicts hemolysis index within 8.3% of experimental measurements with all RH values below the 1.0 acceptance criterion. Six factors not assessed are consistent with MRL 2 scoping. Uncertainty in aleatory sources (blood rheological variability, inter-donor hematocrit spread, rotational speed fluctuations) is discussed in the assessment narrative and acknowledged as within acceptable bounds for the intended decision, though formal UQ artifacts have not been linked to all individual validation results. The overall evidence package supports acceptance of the CFD model for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
